scripts/ - tee-vfhe-bgvrns (BGV prototype) setup, build, and run scripts

All scripts use `set -euo pipefail` and are safe to run multiple times
(idempotent where possible). Run them from the repo root.

SETUP & BUILD
=============

setup_tdx_env.sh
    Verify and configure the TDX + OpenFHE build environment.
    - Installs cmake via yum if missing.
    - Verifies GCC >= 9 and cmake >= 3.16.3.
    - Configures /etc/sgx_default_qcnl.conf with a PCCS_URL (warns and
      continues if the file cannot be created).
    - Verifies TDX attestation is available (/dev/tdx-attest or
      libtdx_attest linkage).
    - Updates the dynamic linker cache for /usr/local/lib.

build_openfhe.sh
    Download, build, and install OpenFHE v1.5.1 to /usr/local.
    - Fetches the v1.5.1 release tarball and the cereal header-only
      submodule (the tarball does not include git submodules).
    - Configures with Release, shared libs, native optimizations;
      disables examples/tests/benchmarks/extras.
    - Builds with make -j$(nproc) (falls back to -j4 on OOM).
    - Installs and runs ldconfig.

build_project.sh
    Configure and build tee-vfhe-bgvrns (server, client, benchmark runner).
    - Runs cmake + make in tee-vfhe-bgvrns/build/.
    - Reconfigures only when CMakeCache.txt is missing or CMakeLists.txt
      changed; otherwise preserves the existing build.
    - Verifies tee_server, tee_client, and benchmark_runner exist and are
      executable in tee-vfhe-bgvrns/build/.

RUN
===

run_server.sh [--port PORT] [extra args...]
    Start the BGV TDX+FHE server in the foreground (default port 8080, or
    $PORT env var). Extra args are passed through to tee_server.
    Press Ctrl+C to stop.

run_client.sh [--host HOST] [--port PORT] [--workload ID]
              [--expected-mr-td HEX] [extra args...]
    Run the BGV client against a started server.
    Defaults: host 127.0.0.1, port 8080 (or $PORT), workload toy.
    If --expected-mr-td is not given, reads the default from
    scripts/expected_mrtd.txt (96 hex chars = 48-byte MR_TD).

INTEGRATION TEST
================

integration_test.sh
    Full end-to-end integration test for tee-vfhe-bgvrns.
    - Builds the project (build_project.sh).
    - Starts the server, runs the client (workload=toy), stops the server.
    - Restarts the server and runs the benchmark_runner with
      --host 127.0.0.1 --port PORT --expected-mr-td HEX, capturing stdout
      (CSV) to a file.
    - Runs ctest.
    - Verifies: client exit 0, transcript/attestation verification pass,
      benchmark_runner exit 0, ctest exit 0, CSV has 11 lines (header +
      10 BGV workloads: noop, toy, small, medium, micro_add, micro_mul,
      micro_modswitch, micro_rotate, app_matvec, app_inference).

BGV WORKLOADS (10)
==================

  noop            Identity pass-through (returns input ciphertext).
  toy             EvalMult of two vectors (c1 * c2 mod 65537).
  small           Dot product via EvalMult + EvalSum (32-element).
  medium          64x64 matrix-vector multiply (masked diagonal method).
  micro_add       EvalAdd(ct_a, ct_b).
  micro_mul       EvalMult(ct_a, ct_b).
  micro_modswitch ModReduce(ct_a) - preserves plaintext, drops RNS limb.
  micro_rotate    EvalRotate(ct_a, 1).
  app_matvec      Application-level matrix-vector multiply (power-of-two
                   rotation keys to bound memory).
  app_inference   Application-level inference workload.

FILES
=====

expected_mrtd.txt
    Default expected MR_TD value (96 hex chars) used by run_client.sh
    when --expected-mr-td is not provided. Contains the current TDX
    guest MR_TD measurement.
